[The efforts to intensify surveillance for the presence of YF in monkeys in the area and to vaccinate people in the area is prudent. The dead howler monkey was found near the border of Santa Catarina. There have been several monkey deaths from yellow fever this year [2021] in Santa Catarina state. The number of human cases has increased from 2 reported on 11 Mar 2021 (see Yellow fever - Americas (05): Brazil (SC) human, monkey 20210315.8247346) to 3 (see Yellow fever - Americas (08): Brazil (SC) 20210413.8305780). These human cases represent spillover from the sylvan (forest) transmission cycle. Fortunately, there has been no urban yellow fever transmission in Brazil since 1942.

Increased surveillance is important to know where yellow fever virus transmission is taking place. People living in these localities should be vaccinated to avoid more human cases. - Mod.TY

